<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 08 at 8:21AM EST  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...INCREASED FIRE DANGER IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM EST THIS MORNING
THROUGH 8 PM EST THIS EVENING...
Very dry air will continue across the region today, with relative
humidity percentages falling into the teens to lower 20`s this
afternoon. Meanwhile, brush and other surface fuels continue to
dry out. Although winds will be less gusty than yesterday, the
combination of very dry air and fuels will increase fire danger
across the area again today.
Please refer to your local burn permitting authorities on whether
you can burn today. If you do burn, use extreme caution since
fires can quickly get out of hand under these conditions.</description>
